<typeStatus box="[552,650,1355,1378]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">syntypes</typeStatus>
deposited in 
<collectionCode box="[804,885,1355,1379]" country="Denmark" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/mci8-ehqk" name="Zoological Museum, University of Copenhagen" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">ZMUC</collectionCode>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Zimsen" box="[939,1088,1354,1379]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" refString="Zimsen, E. (1964) The type material of I. C. Fabricius. Munksgaard, Copenhagen, 656 pp." type="book" year="1964">
Zimsen 
<number box="[1031,1088,1354,1379]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="1964.0">1964</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) were examined in connection with the present study (
<figureCitation box="[413,551,1389,1414]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 25" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1441,1463]" captionTargetBox="[171,1422,192,1405]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,175,1460]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 25. Two syntypes of Cimex vahlii Fabricius, 1787 and their labels. Fig. 20, syntype  1, dorsal view; Fig. 21, same, ventral view; Fig. 22, syntype  2, dorsal view; Fig. 23, same, ventral view; Fig. 24, same, label; Fig. 25, labels pinned in the bottom of the drawer next to the specimens. Scales in mm, Figs. 24 – 25 not to scale (© ZMUC)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255500/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">
Figs. 
<number box="[476,551,1389,1414]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="22.5" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="20.0">20–25</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1181,1938]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">
Other than of 
<taxonomicName box="[362,460,1423,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis box="[362,460,1423,1448]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, only one valid species of 
<taxonomicName box="[773,921,1423,1448]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[773,921,1423,1448]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Brachyplatys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with similar extensive yellow fasciae on the abdominal venter is recognized in Indomalaya, namely 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1867" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1867" box="[827,1168,1458,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="picturifrons">
<emphasis box="[827,997,1459,1483]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. picturifrons</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Walker" box="[1012,1168,1458,1483]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" refString="Walker, F. (1867) Catalogue of the specimens of Heteropterous-Hemiptera in the collection of the British Museum. Part I. Scutata. Trustees of the British Museum, London, 240 pp." type="book" year="1867">
Walker, 
<number box="[1112,1168,1458,1483]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="1867.0">1867</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(Sulawesi). Based on topotypic specimens examined it certainly differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[780,876,1493,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis box="[780,876,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at species level. 
<taxonomicName box="[1072,1292,1493,1518]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis box="[1072,1292,1493,1518]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Brachyplatys vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, is apparently a complex of morphologically similar species readily recognizable based on the genital capsules of the males. Based on the reexamination of the 
<typeStatus box="[621,669,1563,1587]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">type</typeStatus>
material of several species currently recognized as junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName box="[186,285,1597,1622]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis box="[186,285,1597,1622]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy" box="[346,517,1597,1622]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W. (1909) Catalogue of the Hemiptera (Heteroptera) with biological and anatomical references, lists of foodplants and parasites, etc. Vol. I. Cimicidae. Berlin, xl + 392 pp." type="book" year="1909">
Kirkaldy 
<number box="[458,517,1598,1622]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="1909.0">1909</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Davidova-Vilimova" box="[532,824,1597,1622]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" refString="Davidova-Vilimova, J. (2006) Family Plataspidae Dallas, 1851. In: Aukema, B. &amp; Rieger, Ch. (Eds.), Catalogue of the Heteroptera of the Palaearctic Region. Volume 5. Pentatomomorpha II. The Netherlands Entomological Society, Amsterdam, pp. 150 - 165." type="book chapter" year="2006">
Davidová-Vilímová 
<number box="[766,824,1597,1622]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="2006.0">2006</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) some of these species represent valid species. The complex is therefore in need of revision. The situation is complicated further by the fact that the 
<typeStatus box="[1229,1277,1632,1656]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">type</typeStatus>
material of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists of two females from an unspecified locality (“ 
<collectingCountry box="[828,889,1666,1691]" name="India" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">India</collectingCountry>
orientalis” [= East Indies], incorporating usually the whole Indomalaya or at least the Malay Archipelago and Indochina). This problem is not examined further in the present study, the main goal of treating the species here is to call the attention on its differences from 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subaeneus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. subaeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="149" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1181,1938]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,1805,1830]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[361,582,1805,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis box="[361,582,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Brachyplatys vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed throughout the Indomalaya, and it was also recorded from Wallacea and New 
<collectingCountry box="[436,521,1841,1866]" name="Guinea-Bissau" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">Guinea</collectingCountry>
. Several specimens were seen from the Indian Subcontinent, Indochina, and the Malay Archipelago. Because of the broad recognition of this species, some of the old records, however, might need correction. The following remarks are made:
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1977,2035]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">
<number box="[151,166,1978,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="1.0">1</number>
. The redescription (p. 
<number box="[447,476,1977,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="54.0">54</number>
) and illustration (plate IV, fig. 
<number box="[839,853,1978,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="8.0">8</number>
) of 
<taxonomicName box="[904,1055,1977,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subaeneus">
<emphasis box="[904,1055,1977,2002]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. subaeneus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
provided by 
<bibRefCitation author="Vollenhoven" box="[1211,1436,1977,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" refString="Vollenhoven, S. C. S. van (1863) Essai d'une faune entomologique de l'Archipel Indo-Neerlandais. Premiere monographie: Famille des Scutellerides. Martinus Nijhoff, La Haye, 60 pp., IV plates." type="book" year="1863">
Vollenhoven (
<number box="[1370,1428,1977,2002]" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" value="1863.0">1863</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
leave no doubt that the species in concern is 
<taxonomicName box="[701,796,2010,2035]" class="Insecta" family="Hemiptera" genus="Brachyplatys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vahlii">
<emphasis box="[701,796,2010,2035]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="148">B. vahlii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/255500/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="149" targetBox="[171,1422,192,1405]" targetPageId="8">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1440,1524]" pageId="8" pageNumber="149">
